The paper deals with interference channels and signal optimization, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses cooperation between players and achievable rate regions, which are topics related to networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes the usage of rank one signals for simplicity and ease of implementation, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.MM).
